article.headline: Houston 53, South Florida 52
article.story: HOUSTON (AP) -- Lanny Smith hit a 3-pointer with 1:05 left, and Anwar Ferguson blocked a shot with 2 seconds remaining to secure Houston's 53-52 win over South Florida on Saturday night. Smith had missed a game-tying layup about a minute before his 3-pointer. He had another chance to seal the game, but USF's Gerrick Morris recorded his 10th block on Smith's layup attempt with 10 seconds left. That gave USF one last shot, but Ferguson blocked Bradley Mosley's jumper for the win. Smith led Houston (9-15, 3-10 Conference USA) with 15 points, and Andre Owens added 12. Terrence Leather scored 22 points and grabbed 14 rebounds for South Florida (7-16, 1-11). Morris had 8 points and 14 rebounds. USF took a 39-37 lead on Mosley's two free throws with 13:44 left and never trailed until Smith's 3-pointer. Houston won despite shooting just 36 percent from the field. USF shot 38 percent.
